ase-of-coronavirus-128580-2020/ |archive-date=28 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>On 29 February, In [[Qatar]], the first infection in a citizen evacuated from Iran was reported.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/02/qatar-reports-coronavirus-case-citizen-iran-200229144225648.html |title=Qatar reports first coronavirus case in citizen who was in Iran |date=29 February 2020 |publisher=Al Jazeera |access-date=3 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229165654/https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/02/qatar-reports-coronavirus-case-citizen-iran-200229144225648.html |archive-date=29 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n[[Image:13981214000744637189356214810969 \u0646\u0634\u0633\u062a \u0645\u062f\u06cc\u0631\u0627\u0646 \u0634\u0647\u0631\u06cc \u0628\u0627 \u0646\u0645\u0627\u06cc\u0646\u062f\u06af\u0627\u0646 \u0633\u0627\u0632\u0645\u0627\u0646 \u0628\u0647\u062f\u0627\u0634\u062a \u062c\u0647\u0627\u0646\u06cc.jpg|thumb|250px|[[World Health Organization]] representatives holding joint meeting with Tehran administrators]]\nOn 1 March 2020, Armenia announced its first case of coronavirus infection, identified in a man who had returned from Iran.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.rferl.org/a/armenia-identifies-first-coronavirus-man-returning-iran/30462231.html |title=Armenia Identifies First Coronavirus Case As Man Returning From Iran |date=1 March 2020 |work=Radio Free Europe Radio Liberty |access-date=3 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303092218/https://www.rferl.org/a/armenia-identifies-first-coronavirus-man-returning-iran/30462231.html |archive-date=3 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>On 5 March, [[India]] Delhi confirmed a case of a citizen who recently travelled to Iran.\n[[Thailand]] announced the 46th and 47th confirmed cases of the country, a 22-year-old Chinese and 20-year-old Thai, who had recently travelled to Iran.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pr.moph.go.th/?url=pr/detail/2/04/139480|t