ntry)|Georgia]] suspended flights to and from Iran.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://agenda.ge/en/news/2020/558 |title=Georgia suspends direct flights with Iran amid coronavirus outbreak |work=Agenda.ge |date=23 February 2020 |access-date=3 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303134819/https://agenda.ge/en/news/2020/558 |archive-date=3 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> On the same day, [[Pakistan]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.geo.tv/latest/273901-pakistan-seals-taftan|title=Pakistan seals Taftan border after coronavirus situation deteriorates in Iran|date=23 February 2020|website=geo.tv|access-date=23 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200223165746/https://www.geo.tv/latest/273901-pakistan-seals-taftan|archive-date=23 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Turkey]],<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-turkey/turkey-shuts-iran-border-halts-flights-due-to-coronavirus-idUSKCN20H0GH|title=Turkey shuts Iran border, halts flights due to coronavirus|date=23 February 2020|agency=Reuters|access-date=23 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200223203508/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-turkey/turkey-shuts-iran-border-halts-flights-due-to-coronavirus-idUSKCN20H0GH|archive-date=23 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Afghanistan]], and [[Armenia]] closed their land borders with Iran.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.aljazeera.com/amp/news/2020/02/neighbours-close-borders-iran-virus-concerns-rise-200223160135283.html|title=Neighbours close borders with Iran as virus concerns rise|publisher=Al Jazeera|access-date=24 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200224050602/https://www.aljazeera.com/amp/news/2020/02/neighbours-close-borders-iran-virus-concerns-rise-200223160135283.html|archive-date=24 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Afghanistan stopped all forms of travel to and from Iran with three suspected cases reported, while Turkey stopped all incoming flights from Iran.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/feb/23/turkey-and-pakistan-close-borders-with-iran-over-coronavirus-deaths|title=Turkey and Pakistan close borders with Iran over coronavirus deaths|first=Patrick|last=Wintour|date=23 February 2020|work=The Guardian|access-date=25 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200225224333/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/feb/23/turkey-and-pakistan-close-borders-with-iran-over-coronavirus-deaths|archive-date=25 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.arabnews.com/node/1632051/world |title=Pakistan, Turkey, Armenia close Iranian border, Afghanistan bans travel over coronavirus fears |first1=Naimat |last1=Khan |first2=Sayed |last2=Salahuddin |date=27 February 2020 |work=Arab News |access-date=3 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200225205628/https://www.arabnews.com/node/1632051/world |archive-date=25 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>On 24 February, [[Iraq]], [[Kuwait]], [[Oman]], [[Tajikistan]],<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.rferl.org/a/tajikistan-suspends-flights-to-iran-over-coronavirus/30451515.html |title=Tajikistan Suspends Flights To Iran Over Coronavirus |date=24 February 2020 |publisher=Radio Free Europe/Radio Liberty |access-date=28 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200228225220/https://www.rferl.org/a/tajikistan-suspends-flights-to-iran-over-coronavirus/30451515.html |archive-date=28 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> restricted and suspended all flights from and to Iran.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/world/kuwait-bahrain-announce-first-covid-19-cases-12464358|title=Kuwait, Bahrain, Iraq report coronavirus cases linked to Iran|publisher=Channel NewsAsia|date=24 February 2020|access-date=24 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200224203107/https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/world/kuwait-bahrain-announce-first-covid-19-cases-12464358|archive-date=24 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref Name= oman>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-oman/oman-reports-first-two-cases-of-coronavirus-halts-flights-to-iran-tv-idUSKCN20I1LL|title=Oman reports first two cases of coronavirus, halts flights to Iran: TV|agency=Reuters|date=24 February 2020|access-date=24 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200224203107/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-oman/oman-reports-first-two-cases-of-coronavirus-halts-flights-to-iran-tv-idUSKCN20I1LL|archive-date=24 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The citizens of the United Arab Emirates were banned from traveling to Iran.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2020-02-24/kuwait-bahrain-report-cases-of-coronavirus-linked-to-iran|title=U.A.E. Bans Citizens From Iran Travel as Virus Cases Climb|website=Bloomberg|date=24 February 2020|access-date=24 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200224103359/https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2020-02-24/kuwait-bahrain-report-cases-of-coronavirus-linked-to-iran|archive-date=24 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Armenia]] also suspended flights to Iran but scheduled flights to repatriate its citizens from Iran.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.rferl.org/a/armenia-coronavirus-repatriate-citizens-iran/30453491.html |title=Armenia To Repatriate Citizens From Iran Amid Coronavirus Outbreak |date=25 February 2020 |work=Radio Free Europe Radio Liberty |access-date=3 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303042815/https://www.rferl.org/a/armenia-coronavirus-repatriate-citizens-iran/30453491.html |archive-date=3 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 26 February, [[Kazakhstan]] announced a plan to stop flights to and from Iran starting 1 March 2020.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://en.radiofarda.com/a/world-braces-for-spread-of-new-virus-as-more-countries-report-first-cases/30455787.html |title=Kazakhstan Suspending Flights To Iran Over Coronavirus; Russia Issues Travel Warning |date=26 February 2020 |work=Radio Farda |access-date=3 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227160356/https://en.radiofarda.com/a/world-braces-for-spread-of-new-virus-as-more-countries-report-first-cases/30455787.html |archive-date=27 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>On 27 February,Russia announced that it will limit flights to and from Iran except for those operated by [[Aeroflot]] and [[Mahan Air]], and will also stop issuing visas to Iranian citizens starting 28 February 2020.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-russia-iran/russia-suspends-some-flights-between-russia-and-iran-over-coronavirus-idUSKCN20L2D3 |title=Russia suspends some flights between Russia and Iran over coronavirus |agency=Reuters |date=27 February 2020 |access-date=3 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303142334/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-russia-iran/russia-suspends-some-flights-between-russia-and-iran-over-coronavirus-idUSKCN20L2D3 |archive-date=3 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>New Zealand announced temporary restrictions on people travelling from Iran.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.stuff.co.nz/national/health/119899280/ministry-of-health-gives-latest-update-on-novel-coronavirus|title=Coronavirus: First case of virus in New Zealand|website=Stuff|access-date=29 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200228171221/https://www.stuff.co.nz/national/health/119899280/ministry-of-health-gives-latest-update-on-novel-coronavirus|archive-date=28 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Malaysia set up separate immigration lanes for travellers from countries with major COVID-19 outbreaks, including Iran.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asia/coronavirus-malaysia-bars-south-korea-travellers-covid-19-12480676|title=COVID-19: Malaysia bars travellers from South Korea, confirms 2 new cases|website=CNA|access-date=29 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229012254/https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asia/coronavirus-malaysia-bars-south-korea-travellers-covid-19-12480676|archive-date=29 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The United States [[Centers for Disease Control and Prevention]] (CDC) upgraded the status of Iran to level 3 (avoid non-essential travels due to widespread community transmission).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://wwwnc.cdc.gov/travel/notices/warning/coronavirus-iran|title=Coronavirus in Iran \u2013 Warning \u2013 Level 3, Avoid Nonessential Travel \u2013 Travel Health Notices {{!}} Travelers' Health {{!}} CDC|website=wwwnc.cdc.gov|access-date=29 February 2020}}</ref>On 29 February, Australia announced a ban on foreigners arriving directly from Iran, and required them to stay in a third country for 14 days before entering Australia. A woman returning from Iran had also tested positive for the virus.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2020-02-29/australia-announces-iran-travel-ban/12013884 |title=Australia announces Iran travel ban amid COVID-19 coronavirus outbreak |first=Dan |last=Conifer |date=29 February 2020 |work=ABC |access-date=29 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229073205/https://www.abc.net.au/news/2020-02-29/australia-announces-iran-travel-ban/12013884 |archive-date=29 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> [[Azerbaijan]] later closed its border with Iran as two Azeri citizens were confirmed to have been infected in Iran.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-iran-azerbaijan/azerbaijan-closes-border-with-iran-over-coronavirus-concerns-idUSKBN20N0MY |title=Azerbaijan shuts border with Iran over coronavirus concern |date=29 February 2020 |agency=Reuters |access-date=1 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200301055729/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-iran-azerbaijan/azerbaijan-closes-border-with-iran-over-coronavirus-concerns-idUSKBN20N0MY |archive-date=1 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> \n\nOn 2 March 2020, Sweden announced that it had suspended flights operated by [[Iran Air]], the first country to ban flights by the airline.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.thelocal.se/20200302/sweden-bans-flights-from-iran-over-coronavirus-fears |title=Sweden halts flights from Iran over coronavirus fears |work=The Local Sweden |access-date=3 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303140158/https://www.thelocal.se/20200302/sweden-bans-flights-from-iran-over-coronavirus-fears |archive-date=3 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>On 4 March 2020, Thailand declared that people travelling from Iran must be quarantined for 14 days after arriving with no exception.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://mgronline.com/qol/detail/9630000021535|title=\"\u0e2d\u0e19\u0e38\u0e17\u0e34\u0e19\" \u0e40\u0e0b\u0e47\u0e19\u0e1b\u0e23\u0e30\u0e01\u0e32\u0e28 \u0e2a\u0e18.\u0e01\u0e33\u0e2b\u0e19\u0e14 9 \u0e1b\u0e23\u0e30\u0e40\u0e17\u0e28\u0e40\u0e1b\u0e47\u0e19\u0e40\u0e02\u0e15\u0e15\u0e34\u0e14\u0e42\u0e23\u0e04\u0e15\u0e34\u0e14\u0e15\u0e48\u0e2d\u0e2d\u0e31\u0e19\u0e15\u0e23\u0e32\u0e22 \u0e17\u0e38\u0e01\u0e04\u0e19\u0e17\u0e35\u0e48\u0e40\u0e14\u0e34\u0e19\u0e17\u0e32\u0e07\u0e21\u0e32\u0e15\u0e49\u0e2d\u0e07\u0e01\u0e31\u0e01\u0e15\u0e31\u0e27 14 \u0e27\u0e31\u0e19 \u0e2a\u0e01\u0e31\u0e14\u0e42\u0e04\u0e27\u0e34\u0e14-19|date=4 March 2020|access-date=5 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200304074612/https://mgronline.com/qol/detail/9630000021535|archive-date=4 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Iraq]] and [[Azerbaijan]] stopped letting trucks and imports coming from Iran to enter this country, earlier on 29 February Azerbaijan had closed its borders to the people coming from Iran.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.radiofarda.com/a/azerbaijan-and-iraq-close-borders-to-imports-from-iran/30470820.html|title=Azerbaijan And Iraq Close Borders To Imports From Iran|website=RFE/RL|accessdate=8 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200306152239/https://en.radiofarda.com/a/azerbaijan-and-iraq-close-borders-to-imports-from-iran/30470820.html|archive-date=6 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>On 6 March 2020, Russia announced that it will temporary ban visitors arriving from Iran starting 7 March 2020.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.aa.com.tr/en/health/russia-closes-border-with-iran-over-coronavirus-fears/1757573 |title=Russia closes border with Iran over coronavirus fears |first=Elena |last=Teslova |date=7 March 2020 |publisher=Anadolu Agency |access-date=8 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200307191959/https://www.aa.com.tr/en/health/russia-closes-border-with-iran-over-coronavirus-fears/1757573 |archive-date=7 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==Other international reactions==\nOne [[Dubai]]-based newspaper wrongly claimed in a front-page headline that all cases of the new coronavirus in the region came from the Islamic Republic. That would be convenient for the United Arab Emirates, a federation of seven sheikhdoms home to Dubai whose 13 coronavirus cases predominantly trace back to China.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://apnews.com/40a57a17ae66afbc7ce99494fd71a618|title=Virus response in Mideast tainted by political views of Iran|date=27 February 2020|website=AP NEWS|access-date=17 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302144926/https://apnews.com/40a57a17ae66afbc7ce99494fd71a618|archive-date=2 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nBrian Hook, the US State Department's envoy on Iran, said that the Iranian government lied \"and their media was instructed not to report on the coronavirus outbreak as it rapidly spread from the religious city of Qom to other cities\".<ref name=\"newyorker1\"/> The US Secretary of State [[Mike Pompeo]] made a number of accusation against Khamenei in March, saying that Khamanei had lied about the outbreak in Iran and continued to keep [[Mahan Air]] flying to and from China in February, spreading the virus and putting lives at risk, as well as jailing those who spoke out, and that funds for coronavirus had been stolen by officials.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.state.gov/khameneis-lies-about-the-wuhan-virus-put-lives-at-risk/ |title=Khamenei's Lies About the Wuhan Virus Put Lives at Risk |first=Michael R. |last=Pompeo |date=23 March 2020 |access-date=28 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200328115902/https://www.state.gov/khameneis-lies-about-the-wuhan-virus-put-lives-at-risk/ |archive-date=28 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://en.radiofarda.com/a/pompeo-tells-khamenei-speaking-the-truth-to-iranians-best-biological-defense-/30485446.html |title=Pompeo Tells Khamenei Speaking The Truth To Iranians 'Best Biological Defense' |date=13 March 2020 |work=Radio Farda |access-date=28 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200328124411/https://en.radiofarda.com/a/pompeo-tells-khamenei-speaking-the-truth-to-iranians-best-biological-defense-/30485446.html |archive-date=28 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.ibtimes.sg/iran-officials-stole-1-bln-coronavirus-funds-pompeo-says-pushback-against-khamenei-41615 |title=Iran officials stole $1 bln of coronavirus funds, Pompeo says in pushback against Khamenei |date=24 March 2020 |access-date=28 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200328115905/https://www.ibtimes.sg/iran-officials-stole-1-bln-coronavirus-funds-pompeo-says-pushback-against-khamenei-41615 |archive-date=28 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nThe resistance units of the exiled opposition [[People's Mujahedin of Iran]] (MEK) accused the Iranian government of covering up the true death toll, and gave considerably higher death count, up to 20 times higher than the official figures.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.upi.com/Top_News/Voices/2020/03/04/Iranian-regime-hides-truth-about-coronavirus/7741583347380/ |title=Iranian Regime Hides Truth about Coronavirus |agency=United Press International |date=4 March 2020 |access-date=5 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305133659/https://www.upi.com/Top_News/Voices/2020/03/04/Iranian-regime-hides-truth-about-coronavirus/7741583347380/ |archive-date=5 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"france24\">{{cite news |url=https://www.france24.com/en/20200301-what-is-the-real-size-of-the-coronavirus-epidemic-in-iran |title=What is the real size of the coronavirus epidemic in Iran? |date=1 March 2020 |publisher=France 24 |access-date=6 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305163602/https://www.france24.com/en/20200301-what-is-the-real-size-of-the-coronavirus-epidemic-in-iran |archive-date=5 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> According to Radio farda, In a joint statement, in late March 2020, one hundred Iranian activists blamed the Supreme Leader, Ali Khamenei, and President Hassan Rouhani for covering up the spread of corona virus and turning it into a catastrophe affecting whole of the country. All of the signatories including a [[Chemistry]] expert and an former adviser to the [[International Atomic Energy Agency]] (IAEA) live outside of Iran.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.radiofarda.com/a/one-hundred-iranian-activists-blame-khamenei-for-severity-of-coronavirus-outbreak/30516266.html|title=One Hundred Activists Blame Khamenei For Severity Of Coronavirus Outbreak in Iran|website=RFE/RL|access-date=30 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200330133755/https://en.radiofarda.com/a/one-hundred-iranian-activists-blame-khamenei-for-severity-of-coronavirus-outbreak/30516266.html|archive-date=30 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n===Humanitarian assistance===\nThe UN's Children Fund ([[UNICEF]]) has flown aid into Iran. In late February, the first cargo plane with [[Personal Protective Equipment]] (PPE) arrived, another on 3 March and a third aircraft on 16 March. On 3 March, the [[United Arab Emirates]] sent an aircraft with medical supplies and five [[WHO]] experts. [[Uzbekistan]] sent a plane on 16 March.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ifpnews.com/unicef-uae-uzbekistan-send-aid-to-iran-amid-coronavirus-outbreak|title=UNICEF, UAE, Uzbekistan Send Aid to Iran amid Coronavirus Outbreak|first=IFP Editorial|last=Staff|date=17 March 2020|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320080754/https://ifpnews.com/unicef-uae-uzbekistan-send-aid-to-iran-amid-coronavirus-outbreak|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe fifth batch of testing kits was dispatched to Iran by the [[World Health Organization]] on 28 February.<ref name=\"financial\"/> The group of Chinese medical experts with a new pack of humanitarian aid entered Iran on 29 February.<ref name=\"financial\">{{Cite news|url=https://financialtribune.com/articles/national/102401/more-int-l-medical-aid-arrives-in-iran|title=More Int'l Medical Aid Arrives in Iran|date=29 February 2020|agency=financial tribune|access-date=29 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200301004140/https://financialtribune.com/articles/national/102401/more-int-l-medical-aid-arrives-in-iran|archive-date=1 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The [[Ministry of National Defense of the People's Republic of China|Chinese Defense Ministry]] announced on 20 March that test kits, protective suits and medical masks provided by the [[People's Liberation Army]] were handed to the [[Armed Forces of the Islamic Republic of Iran]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.armyrecognition.com/march_2020_news_defense_global_security_army_industry/chinese_army_donates_medical_supplies_to_iranian_army_to_fight_coronavirus.html |title=Archived copy |access-date=23 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321051219/https://www.armyrecognition.com/march_2020_news_defense_global_security_army_industry/chinese_army_donates_medical_supplies_to_iranian_army_to_fight_coronavirus.html |archive-date=21 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn 23 March 2020, the [[European Union]] pledged \u20ac20m in humanitarian assistance to the Gulf nation. The union said that it was committed to help Iran combat the [[2019\u20132020 coronavirus pandemic|coronavirus pandemic]] and informed that it would further support its plea for IMF financial help.<ref>{{cite_web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/health-coronavirus-eu-iran/eu-to-provide-20-mln-euros-in-humanitarian-aid-to-iran-idUSL8N2BG6OK|title=EU to provide 20 mln euros in humanitarian aid to Iran|accessdate=23 March 2020|agency=Reuters|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324034339/https://www.reuters.com/article/health-coronavirus-eu-iran/eu-to-provide-20-mln-euros-in-humanitarian-aid-to-iran-idUSL8N2BG6OK|archive-date=24 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===US sanctions===\nThe US sanctions have made difficulties for the governmental and non-governmental institutions to provide medication for people who are infected by the Coronavirus. Sending medical supplies to Iran through the recently established Swiss channel requires a written permission from the US. Recently, sanctions on 12 new Iranian entities were imposed by the US Department of State. However, according to the Trump administration, Iran is using sanctions \"as an excuse to hide their own incompetence, including a reluctance to take the necessary tough measures to restrict population movements.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/18/uk-presses-us-to-ease-iran-sanctions-to-help-fight-coronavirus |title=UK presses US to ease Iran sanctions to help fight coronavirus |work=The Guardian |access-date=18 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320191936/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/18/uk-presses-us-to-ease-iran-sanctions-to-help-fight-coronavirus |archive-date=20 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nWhile the [[United States sanctions against Iran|US sanctions]] legally allow pharmaceuticals and humanitarian products to be sold to Iran, due to their nature, very few banks are willing to risk sanctions by trading with Iran.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-51642926|title=Iran Corona Virus|date=29 February 2020|agency=BBC|access-date=29 February 2020|quote=But Iran says companies find it difficult to process payments with banks unwilling to risk breaking US rules and risk sanctions themselves|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200228031515/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-51642926|archive-date=28 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://foreignpolicy.com/2020/03/03/iran-coronavirus-spreads-sanctions-covid19-iranian-doctors-fear-worst/|title=As Coronavirus Spreads, Iranian Doctors Fear the Worst|date=6 March 2020|work=Foreign Affairs|access-date=6 March 2020|quote=Should Iranian manufacturers run out of these raw materials, it will be very difficult, if not impossible, to effectively contain and treat COVID-19 in Iran.|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200304133129/https://foreignpolicy.com/2020/03/03/iran-coronavirus-spreads-sanctions-covid19-iranian-doctors-fear-worst/|archive-date=4 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> This has severely limited the medical supplies available to the Iranian public health system in dealing with the coronavirus outbreak. One right wing lobby group in the United States, [[United Against Nuclear Iran]], has argued to stop all global humanitarian trade with Iran and prevent medical supplies from reaching the country.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://theintercept.com/2020/03/05/iran-coronavirus-medicine-sanctions/|title=Amid Coronavirus Outbreak, Trump-Aligned Pressure Group Pushes to Stop Medicine Sales to Iran|date=6 March 2020|access-date=6 March 2020|quote=UANI\u2019s efforts, however, have extended beyond sanctions into pressuring companies that do legal trade with Iran, often under the Treasury Department\u2019s humanitarian exemptions to sanctions \u2014 including medical-related trades that would presumably aid in combating a massive public health crisis like this coronavirus outbreak.|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200306000824/https://theintercept.com/2020/03/05/iran-coronavirus-medicine-sanctions/|archive-date=6 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIran's President [[Hassan Rouhani]] wrote public letter to world leaders asking for help, saying that his country doesn't have access to international markets due to the [[United States sanctions against Iran]].<ref>{{cite news |title=U.S. sanctions 'severely hamper' Iran coronavirus fight, Rouhani says |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-iran/us-sanctions-severely-hamper-iran-coronavirus-fight-rouhani-idUSKBN2110HL |agency=Reuters |date=14 March 2020 |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319011538/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-iran/us-sanctions-severely-hamper-iran-coronavirus-fight-rouhani-idUSKBN2110HL |archive-date=19 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>The UK, Pakistan, China, the UN High Commissioner for Human Rights, the [[Group of 77]], and experts are pressing the US to ease sanctions on Iran to help it fight the growing coronavirus outbreak.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Wintour|first=Patrick|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/18/uk-presses-us-to-ease-iran-sanctions-to-help-fight-coronavirus|title=UK presses US to ease Iran sanctions to help fight coronavirus|date=18 March 2020|work=The Guardian|access-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live|issn=0261-3077|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320191936/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/18/uk-presses-us-to-ease-iran-sanctions-to-help-fight-coronavirus|archive-date=20 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/03/pakistan-pm-urges-halt-sanctions-coronavirus-hit-iran-200320155952750.html|title=Pakistan PM urges US to halt sanctions on coronavirus-hit Iran|last=Usaid|first=Siddiqui|date=20 March 2020|publisher=Al Jazeera|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321082900/https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/03/pakistan-pm-urges-halt-sanctions-coronavirus-hit-iran-200320155952750.html|archive-date=21 March 2020|access-date=21 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://cepr.net/press-release/us-government-should-immediately-lift-economic-sanctions-to-avoid-causing-more-deaths-from-pandemic-economists-say/|title=US Government Should Immediately Lift Economic Sanctions to Avoid Causing More Deaths From Pandemic, Economists Say|date=18 March 2020|website=Center for Economic and Policy Research|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321082902/https://cepr.net/press-release/us-government-should-immediately-lift-economic-sanctions-to-avoid-causing-more-deaths-from-pandemic-economists-say/|archive-date=21 March 2020|access-date=21 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=U.S. to Iran: Coronavirus won't save you from sanctions |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-iran-usa-idUSKBN21712L |accessdate=22 March 2020 |agency=Reuters |date=20 March 2020  |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321233214/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-iran-usa-idUSKBN21712L |archive-date=21 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.rappler.com/world/global-affairs/255747-united-nations-urges-easing-sanctions-iran-others-coronavirus|title=U.N. urges easing of sanctions on Iran, others facing virus|date=24 March 2020|work=[[Rappler]]|access-date=24 March 2020|url-status=live|agency=[[Agence France-Presse]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324182551/https://www.rappler.com/world/global-affairs/255747-united-nations-urges-easing-sanctions-iran-others-coronavirus|archive-date=24 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.presstv.com/Detail/2020/04/04/622281/G77-China-unilateral-sanctions|title=G77, China urge end to unilateral sanctions amid coronavirus pandemic|date=4 April 2020|publisher=Press TV|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200404213726/https://www.presstv.com/Detail/2020/04/04/622281/G77-China-unilateral-sanctions|archive-date=4 April 2020|access-date=4 April 2020}}</ref> However, fresh sanctions on individuals and companies linked with allegedly linked to the [[Islamic Revolutionary Guard Corps]] (IRGC) and trade with Iran was imposed on 26 March 2020.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/ajimpact/covid-19-rages-slaps-sanctions-iranian-individuals-200326145240630.html |title=As COVID-19 rages, US slaps new sanctions on Iranian individuals |date=26 March 2020 |publisher=Al Jazeera |access-date=1 April 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200401024743/https://www.aljazeera.com/ajimpact/covid-19-rages-slaps-sanctions-iranian-individuals-200326145240630.html |archive-date=1 April 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.middleeasteye.net/news/us-announces-new-sanctions-against-iran-amid-coronavirus-crisis |title=US announces new sanctions against Iran despite coronavirus crisis |date=26 March 2020 |work=Middle East Eye |access-date=1 April 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200331205134/https://www.middleeasteye.net/news/us-announces-new-sanctions-against-iran-amid-coronavirus-crisis |archive-date=31 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Iranian leader Khamenei has also stated that he doesn't \"trust\" that the United States would provide medicine because it could \"spread the virus more\".<ref>{{cite_web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-iran/irans-khamenei-rejects-us-help-offer-vows-to-defeat-coronavirus-idUSKBN21909Y|title=Iran's Khamenei rejects U.S. help offer, vows to defeat coronavirus|accessdate=22 March 2020|agency=Reuters|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200403012415/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-iran/irans-khamenei-rejects-us-help-offer-vows-to-defeat-coronavirus-idUSKBN21909Y|archive-date=3 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=aj>{{cite_web|url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/03/iran-leader-refuses-cites-coronavirus-conspiracy-theory-200322145122752.html|title=Iran leader refuses US help; cites coronavirus conspiracy theory|accessdate=23 March 2020|publisher=Al Jazeera|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322223837/https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/03/iran-leader-refuses-cites-coronavirus-conspiracy-theory-200322145122752.html|archive-date=22 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe United States Government rejected allegations by Iran and asserted that sanctions do not include the import of medicine and medical facilities to Iran. Morgan Ortagus, the spokeswoman for the State Department, suggested that Iran use the funds from [[Execution of Imam Khomeini's Order|Setad]] to fight COVID-19.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://en.radiofarda.com/a/us-tells-khamenei-to-use-billions-in-hedge-fund-to-combat-coronavirus/30519691.html |title=US Tells Khamenei To Use 'Billions In Hedge Fund' To Combat Coronavirus |access-date=2 April 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200401170426/https://en.radiofarda.com/a/us-tells-khamenei-to-use-billions-in-hedge-fund-to-combat-coronavirus/30519691.html |archive-date=1 April 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> (On April 6, Iran announced it would be withdrawing 1 billion Euros from the sovereign wealth fund to fight COVID-19<ref>{{cite news|title=Iran supreme leader approves tapping sovereign wealth fund to fight coronavirus|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-iran-fund/iran-supreme-leader-approves-tapping-sovereign-wealth-fund-to-fight-coronavirus-idUSKBN21O23U}}</ref>)\n\n==Alternative estimates==\n{{POV section|date=March 2020}}\nThe figures given by the [[Iranian Health Ministry]] have been disputed both inside and outside Iran, including by members of the [[Iranian Parliament]]. \n\nIn a [[preprint]] paper pending for review on medRxiv journal, Tuite ''et al.'' estimated that as of 25 February, {{circa}} 18,300 infections (95% confidence interval: 3,770\u201353,470; best-case scenario: 380\u20135,320 cases) could have occurred in Iran, based on known exported case counts and air travel links between Iran and other countries, the latter compiled from the data in the past. They concluded that Iran is likely to experience an \"epidemic of significant size\", while lack of identified cases in countries with close travel ties to Iran are because the cases are \"likely being missed, rather than being truly absent\".<ref name=\"Tuite_18k_Iranian_positives\">{{cite news | last1 = Tuite | first1 = Ashleigh R. | last2 = Bogoch | first2 = Isaac | last3 = Sherbo | first3 = Ryan | last4 = Watts | first4 = Alexander | last5 = Fisman | first5 = David N. | last6 = Khan | first6 = Kamran | title = Estimation of COVID-2019 burden and potential for international dissemination of infection from Iran | date = 25 February 2020 | url = https://www.medrxiv.org/content/10.1101/2020.02.24.20027375v1 | doi = 10.1101/2020.02.24.20027375 | accessdate = 28 February 2020 | archiveurl = https://archive.today/20200227134801/https://www.medrxiv.org/content/10.1101/2020.02.24.20027375v1 | archivedate = 27 February 2020 | url-status = live }}</ref>\n\nThe government of Iran had insisted that there was no confirmed COVID-19 in Iran before 19 February 2020, when the first cases were announced.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ir.voanews.com/a/iran-corona/5296552.html|title=\u0645\u0631\u06af \u0628\u0631 \u0627\u062b\u0631 \u06a9\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627 \u062f\u0631 \u0627\u06cc\u0631\u0627\u0646\u061b \u067e\u0646\u0647\u0627\u0646\u200c\u06a9\u0627\u0631\u06cc \u0645\u0642\u0627\u0645\u0627\u062a\u060c \u0628\u06cc\u200c\u0627\u0639\u062a\u0645\u0627\u062f\u06cc \u0645\u0631\u062f\u0645 \u0631\u0627 \u0627\u0641\u0632\u0627\u06cc\u0634 \u062f\u0627\u062f\u0647 \u0627\u0633\u062a|website=\u0635\u062f\u0627\u06cc \u0622\u0645\u0631\u06cc\u06a9\u0627|language=fa|access-date=23 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200221135557/https://ir.voanews.com/a/iran-corona/5296552.html|archive-date=21 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dw.com/fa-ir/\u062f\u0648-\u0628\u06cc\u0645\u0627\u0631-\u0645\u0628\u062a\u0644\u0627-\u0628\u0647-\u0648\u06cc\u0631\u0648\u0633-\u06a9\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627-\u062f\u0631-\u0642\u0645-\u062f\u0631\u06af\u0630\u0634\u062a\u0646\u062f/a-52435042|title=\u062f\u0648 \u0628\u06cc\u0645\u0627\u0631 \u0645\u0628\u062a\u0644\u0627 \u0628\u0647 \u0648\u06cc\u0631\u0648\u0633 \u06a9\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627 \u062f\u0631 \u0642\u0645 \u062f\u0631\u06af\u0630\u0634\u062a\u0646\u062f {{!}} DW {{!}} 19 February 2020|website=DW.COM|language=fa-IR|access-date=23 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200220135539/https://www.dw.com/fa-ir/%D8%AF%D9%88-%D8%A8%DB%8C%D9%85%D8%A7%D8%B1-%D9%85%D8%A8%D8%AA%D9%84%D8%A7-%D8%A8%D9%87-%D9%88%DB%8C%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%B3-%DA%A9%D8%B1%D9%88%D9%86%D8%A7-%D8%AF%D8%B1-%D9%82%D9%85-%D8%AF%D8%B1%DA%AF%D8%B0%D8%B4%D8%AA%D9%86%D8%AF/a-52435042|archive-date=20 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> However, a letter {{Weasel inline|date=March 2020|text=claimed to be}} from the [[Ministry of Health and Medical Education|Ministry of Health]] to the office of the President that {{Attribution needed|date=March 2020|reason=Who confirmed the authenticity|text=circulated on social media}} suggests that the Iranian authorities were aware of confirmed SARS-CoV-2 cases and deaths {{Weasel inline|date=March 2020|text=many days}} before the official announcement. Government officials said that the letter was a fake.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/persian/iran-51521216|title=\u0648\u0632\u0627\u0631\u062a \u0628\u0647\u062f\u0627\u0634\u062a \u0627\u06cc\u0631\u0627\u0646 \u0627\u0631\u0633\u0627\u0644 \u0646\u0627\u0645\u0647 \u062f\u0631\u0628\u0627\u0631\u0647 \u0645\u0648\u0627\u0631\u062f \u0627\u0628\u062a\u0644\u0627 \u0648 \u0645\u0631\u06af \u062f\u0631 \u0627\u062b\u0631 \u06a9\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627 \u0631\u0627 \u062a\u06a9\u0630\u06cc\u0628 \u06a9\u0631\u062f|date=16 February 2020|work=BBC News \u0641\u0627\u0631\u0633\u06cc|access-date=23 February 2020|language=fa}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.radiozamaneh.com/489362|title=\u0645\u0639\u0627\u0648\u0646 \u0648\u0632\u06cc\u0631 \u0628\u0647\u062f\u0627\u0634\u062a \u0627\u0628\u062a\u0644\u0627\u06cc \u06f4\u06f5 \u0646\u0641\u0631 \u0628\u0647 \u06a9\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627 \u0631\u0627 \u062a\u06a9\u0630\u06cc\u0628 \u06a9\u0631\u062f|date=16 February 2020|work=[[Radio Zamaneh]]|access-date=26 February 2020|language=fa}}</ref> Another letter also {{Attribution needed|date=March 2020|reason=Who confirmed the authenticity|text=circulated on social media;}} it was signed by interior minister [[Abdolreza Rahmani Fazli]] and sent to Health Minister [[Saeed Namaki]] to request that the announcement of coronavirus outbreak be delayed{{by whom|date=March 2020}} until after the [[2020 Iranian legislative election|parliamentary election]] to avoid a low turnout of voters.{{Dubious|date=March 2020}} The government has also denied this claim.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.radiofarda.com/a/iran-health-ministry-denies-letter-warning-related-to-coronavirus-elections/30443145.html|title=\u0646\u0627\u0645\u0647 \u0645\u0646\u062a\u0633\u0628 \u0628\u0647 \u0648\u0632\u06cc\u0631 \u06a9\u0634\u0648\u0631 \u062f\u0631 \u0627\u0631\u062a\u0628\u0627\u0637 \u0628\u0627 \u0627\u0646\u062a\u062e\u0627\u0628\u0627\u062a \u0648 \u0648\u06cc\u0631\u0648\u0633 \u06a9\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627 \u062a\u06a9\u0630\u06cc\u0628 \u0634\u062f|website=\u0631\u0627\u062f\u06cc\u0648 \u0641\u0631\u062f\u0627|language=fa|access-date=23 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200221135004/https://www.radiofarda.com/a/iran-health-ministry-denies-letter-warning-related-to-coronavirus-elections/30443145.html|archive-date=21 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 9 March, [[Graeme Wood (journalist)|Graeme Wood]] stated that he deems the official count \"certainly an undercount\", and provided alternative estimates which he calls \"doomsday figures\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theatlantic.com/ideas/archive/2020/03/irans-coronavirus-problem-lot-worse-it-seems/607663/ |first=Graeme |last=Wood |title=Iran Has Far More Coronavirus Cases Than It Is Letting On |work=The Atlantic |date=9 March 2020 |accessdate=9 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200309232036/https://www.theatlantic.com/ideas/archive/2020/03/irans-coronavirus-problem-lot-worse-it-seems/607663/ |archive-date=9 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n=== World Health Organization verification ===\nOn 28 February 2020, [[Michael J Ryan (doctor)|Michael Ryan]], chief of the WHO health emergencies programme told the press that the mortality rate in Iran indicated its outbreak might be more widespread than realised.<ref name=\"BBC\"/>\n\nOn 2 March 2020, The [[World Health Organization]] director general [[Tedros Adhanom]] said in an interview with CNBC that the WHO has its own mechanism for checking national health authorities' statistics and did not see problems with the official Iranian government SARS-CoV-2 and COVID-19 counts.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cnbc.com/video/2020/03/02/no-evidence-of-iranian-cover-up-in-virus-crisis-so-far-who.html|title=WHO chief says no evidence of Iranian cover-up in virus crisis so far|date=2 March 2020|publisher=CNBC|access-date=5 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303161026/https://www.cnbc.com/video/2020/03/02/no-evidence-of-iranian-cover-up-in-virus-crisis-so-far-who.html|archive-date=3 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 17 March 2020, WHO regional emergency director Rick Brennan said the number of cases reported in Iran could represent only about 20% of the real numbers because testing was restricted to severe cases, as is the case even in some wealthy European countries. He added \"We\u2019ve said the weakest link in their chain is the data. They are rapidly increasing their ability to test and so the numbers will go up... [t]here's a great commitment and they are taking it seriously from the highest level of government\".<ref name=\"WHO estimate\">{{citation|title=WHO to start coronavirus testing in rebel Syria; Iran raises efforts, official says|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-mideast/who-to-start-coronavirus-testing-in-rebel-syria-iran-raises-efforts-official-says-idUSKBN2133PK|first=Emma|last=Farge|editor-first=Grant|editor-last=McCool|agency=Reuters|date=17 March 2020|access-date=17 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200316212446/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-mideast/who-to-start-coronavirus-testing-in-rebel-syria-iran-raises-efforts-official-says-idUSKBN2133PK|archive-date=16 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n=== Other sources ===\n\n==== Iranian officials ====\n[[Masoud Pezeshkian]], the First Deputy of the Parliament of Iran, claimed on 3 March 2020 that the figures reported by Iran's health ministry are \"not real\".<ref>{{cite news |url=https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/03/04/Iran-s-death-toll-due-to-coronavirus-not-real-Iranian-official.html |title=Iran's official figures on coronavirus cases 'not real': Iranian official |date=4 March 2020 |accessdate=5 March 2020 |publisher=[[Al Arabiya English]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200304213114/http://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/03/04/Iran-s-death-toll-due-to-coronavirus-not-real-Iranian-official.html |archive-date=4 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n[[2016 Iranian legislative election|Member of parliament]] for Qom [[Ahmad Amirabadi Farahani]] claimed on 24 February 2020 that COVID-19 had arrived in Qom three weeks prior, in early February, that the first death had occurred on 13 February but was not announced by officials, and that the true number of COVID-19 deaths in Qom was 50.<ref name=\"AJE_Qom_coverup_50deaths\" /><ref>{{cite news |url=https://en.radiofarda.com/a/iran-lawmaker-says-fifty-died-of-coronavirus-in-qom-alone-as-crisis-deepens/30451096.html |title=Iran Lawmaker Says Fifty Died Of Coronavirus in Qom Alone, As Crisis Deepens |date=24 February 2020 |work=Radio Farda |access-date=26 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200225164803/https://en.radiofarda.com/a/iran-lawmaker-says-fifty-died-of-coronavirus-in-qom-alone-as-crisis-deepens/30451096.html |archive-date=25 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Deputy health minister Iraj Harirchi denied giving false figures, and stated that the death count was 12 with a total of 66 infections.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/feb/24/coronavirus-dead-in-iranian-city-of-qom|title=Coronavirus: Iran denies cover-up after reports of 50 deaths|author1=Sam Jones|author2=Aamna Mohdin|date=24 February 2020|work=The Guardian|access-date=24 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200224153012/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/feb/24/coronavirus-dead-in-iranian-city-of-qom|archive-date=24 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nAs two health ministry officials, a former ministry official and three doctors claimed, Iranian authorities of an increasing number of patients with lung infections and high fever in Qom in early January and They didn\u2019t announce the news until weeks later, because of the upcoming elections, held on February 21.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-iran-qom/elections-ties-with-china-shaped-irans-coronavirus-response-idUSKBN21K1NO |title=Elections, ties with China shaped Iran's coronavirus response|work=Reuters |access-date=7 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==== Anonymous sources reported by media ====\nOn 28 February 2020, [[BBC]] reported 210 deaths have occurred in Iran, citing \"sources in the country's health system\", while the official number for the day was 34.<ref name=\"BBC\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-51673053|title=Coronavirus kills 210 in Iran \u2013 hospital sources|date=28 February 2020|work=BBC News|access-date=28 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229151242/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-51673053|archive-date=29 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Kianush Jahanpur, the spokesman for the health ministry rejected the BBC report in a tweet.<ref name=\"BBC_210_deaths_Iran\">{{cite news |url = https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-iran-casualties/at-least-210-people-have-died-from-coronavirus-in-iran-bbc-persian-idUSKCN20M2RL | title=Iran rejects BBC Persian report of at least 210 coronavirus deaths | newspaper=[[Thomson Reuters]] | date=28 February 2020 | accessdate=28 February 2020 |archivedate= 28 February 2020 |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20200228203743/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-iran-casualties/at-least-210-people-have-died-from-coronavirus-in-iran-bbc-persian-idUSKCN20M2RL |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 12 March, ''[[The Economist]]'' wrote \"[s]ome in the government think the actual number of cases is closer to 100,000\", while the official count of infected people was about 9,000.<ref name=\"veconomist\" >{{cite news|title= Iran has let its covid-19 outbreak get out of hand|url= https://www.economist.com/middle-east-and-africa/2020/03/12/iran-has-let-its-covid-19-outbreak-get-out-of-hand|work= [[The Economist]]|date= 12 March 2020|access-date= 13 March 2020|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200312135704/https://www.economist.com/middle-east-and-africa/2020/03/12/iran-has-let-its-covid-19-outbreak-get-out-of-hand|archive-date= 12 March 2020|url-status= live}}</ref>\n\nOn 22 March, [[Radio Farda]] reported that \"based on the statements made by local officials in various parts of Iran\", around 2,372 have died, while the official death toll reached 1,556.<ref name=\"Farda 2020\">{{cite web | title='No Lockdown' Says Rouhani As Nearly 14,000 Iranians Contract COVID-19 | website=Radio Farda | date=15 March 2020 | url=https://en.radiofarda.com/a/no-lockdown-says-rouhani-as-nearly-14-000-iranians-contract-covid-19/30489072.html | access-date=15 March 2020 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200316131034/https://en.radiofarda.com/a/no-lockdown-says-rouhani-as-nearly-14-000-iranians-contract-covid-19/30489072.html | archive-date=16 March 2020 | url-status=live }}</ref> Radio Farda also said on 21 March that since Iran's government statistics only include those who had tested positive for the disease, due to a lack of test kits, deaths may be registered as respiratory complications or [[influenza]]. They put their estimate of the number of infections at 16,000 in Tehran alone when the official figure given was 20,610 for the whole country on that date.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://en.radiofarda.com/a/exclusive-more-than-47-000-coronavirus-patients-in-iran-hospitals-2-216-dead/30501369.html |title=Exclusive: More Than 47,000 Coronavirus Patients In Iran Hospitals, 2,216 Dead |date=21 March 2020 |work=Radio Farda |access-date=28 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200328144213/https://en.radiofarda.com/a/exclusive-more-than-47-000-coronavirus-patients-in-iran-hospitals-2-216-dead/30501369.html |archive-date=28 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==== Satellite imagery from Qom cemetery ====\n[[Image:3407559 \u062a\u062f\u0641\u06cc\u0646 \u0645\u062a\u0648\u0641\u06cc\u0627\u0646 \u0645\u0628\u062a\u0644\u0627 \u0628\u0647 \u06a9\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627 \u062f\u0631 \u0622\u0631\u0627\u0645\u0633\u062a\u0627\u0646 \u0628\u0647\u0634\u062a \u0645\u0639\u0635\u0648\u0645\u0647.jpg|thumb|250px|Burial site at Qom's Behesht Masoumeh Cemetery]]\nOn 12 March, ''[[The Washington Post]]'' published satellite images and analysis provided by [[Maxar Technologies]], saying that vast burial pits were being excavated near Qom, said to be used to accommodate the potentially increasing number of victims in the city. The digging of the new section of burial pits began on 21 February, only two days after the government announced their first cases of COVID-19, and then rapidly expanded. The number of fresh graves suggests preparation for a far larger number of deaths.<ref>*{{cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/graphics/2020/world/iran-coronavirus-outbreak-graves|title=Coronavirus burial pit so vast they're visible from space|first1=Erin|last1=Cunningham|first2=Dalton|last2=Bennett|date=12 March 2020|work=The Washington Post|access-date=13 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200313055935/https://www.washingtonpost.com/graphics/2020/world/iran-coronavirus-outbreak-graves/|archive-date=13 March 2020|url-status=live}}\n*{{YouTube|id=fjuWyXzKBIw|title=Iran is building a massive grave for coronavirus victims}}. published on 13 March 2020 by The Washington Post</ref> Qom municipality official responsible for the city's burial sites said \"the graves had been planned before the outbreak as part of usual procedures in the cemetery\", and some observers pointed that overall length of the purported 100 yards cannot accommodate more than about 75\u2013100 graves.<ref>{{citation|title=Washington Post hypes fake news on coronavirus 'burial pits' in Iran|url=https://www.presstv.com/Detail/2020/03/14/620825/Washington-Post-fake-news-coronavirus-burial-Iran|publisher=Press TV|date=14 March 2020|access-date=14 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200314124434/https://www.presstv.com/Detail/2020/03/14/620825/Washington-Post-fake-news-coronavirus-burial-Iran|archive-date=14 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Statistics==\n{{Graph:Chart\n|type=line\n|colors=#F46D43\n|linewidth=1\n|showSymbols=1\n|width=600\n|showValues=\n|xAxisTitle=Date\n|xAxisAngle=-40\n|x=19/2, 20/2, 21/2, 22/2, 23